p.q:
That, for the purpose of any Act resulting from the Social Security Bill, it is expedient to authorise the following—

(1) The payment out of money provided by Parliament of—

(a) any sums falling to be paid by the Secretary of State by virtue of the Act by way of travelling expenses;

(b) any other expenses of a Minister of the Crown attributable to the Act;

(c) any increase attributable to the Act in the sums payable out of money provided by Parliament under any other Act;

(2) the making of payments into the Consolidated Fund.
